"Crouzeix C., Le Mouël J.-L., Perrier F., Richon P., Morat P.","Long-term thermal evolution and effect of low power heating in an underground quarry [Évolution thermique à long terme d'une carriè souterraine et effet d'un chauffage de faible puissance]",2003,"Comptes Rendus - Geoscience","335","4",,"345","354",,,10.1016/S1631-0713(03)00054-3,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0038209151&partnerID=40&md5=04bbe090db51a53bd1ce4a79e237659d","Lab. de geomagnétisme, Institut de physique du Globe, 4 Place Jussieu, Paris cedex 05 75252, France; Serv.Radioanalyse Chimie Envrn., Commissariat a l'energie atomique, BP 12, Bruyeres-le-Châtel 91680, France","Crouzeix, C., Lab. de geomagnétisme, Institut de physique du Globe, 4 Place Jussieu, Paris cedex 05 75252, France; Le Mouël, J.-L., Lab. de geomagnétisme, Institut de physique du Globe, 4 Place Jussieu, Paris cedex 05 75252, France; Perrier, F., Serv.Radioanalyse Chimie Envrn., Commissariat a l'energie atomique, BP 12, Bruyeres-le-Châtel 91680, France; Richon, P., Serv.Radioanalyse Chimie Envrn., Commissariat a l'energie atomique, BP 12, Bruyeres-le-Châtel 91680, France; Morat, P., Lab. de geomagnétisme, Institut de physique du Globe, 4 Place Jussieu, Paris cedex 05 75252, France","Vertical profiles of temperature have been monitored in the atmosphere of an underground quarry since June 2001. A long-term temperature increase of the order of 0.1 °C per year is observed. Three heating experiments with 100-W sources, performed to study plume dynamics, can also be used to investigate the effect of visits on this increase. Ten days after the 24-h heatings, the initial state is not restored. Artificial contributions to the observed long-term temperature trend, triggered by internal heat release, thus cannot be ruled out. This experiment defines strict criteria for the underground monitoring of global warming or the preservation of painted caves. © 2003 Académie des sciences. Published by Éditions scientifiques et médicales Elsevier SAS. All rights reserved.","Long-term thermal evolution; Low power heating; Resilience; Turbulent plumes; Underground cavity","global warming; perturbation; quarry; resilience; temperature; thermal evolution; thermodynamics; underground construction; water-rock interaction",,,,,,"Baines, W.D., Turner, J.S., Turbulent buoyant convection from a source in a confined region (1969) J. Fluid Mech., 37 (1), pp. 51-80; Dercourt, J., Numéro spécial : L'effet de serre, certitudeset incertitudes (1999) C. R. Acad. Sci. Paris, 328, pp. 221-293. , Ser. IIa; De Freitas, C.R., Littlejohn, R.N., Clarkson, T.S., Kristament, I.S., Cave climate: Assessment of airflow and ventilation (1982) J. Climatol., 2, pp. 383-397; Linden, P.F., Lane-Serff, G.F., Smeed, D.A., Emptying filling boxes: The fluid mechanics of natural ventilation (1990) J. Fluid Mech., 212, pp. 309-335; Mangin, A., Bourges, F., d'Hulst, D., Painted caves conservation: A stability problem in a natural system (the example of the prehistoric cave of Gargas, French Pyrenees) (1999) C. R. Acad. Sci. Paris, 328, pp. 295-301. , Ser. IIa; Moiriat, D., Obert, D., Pothérat, P., Bebien, J., Laroche, M., Évolutiondes désordres dans une carrière souterraine de calcairelutétien (carrière de la Brasserie, bois de Vincennes, Paris) (2000) Bull. Inf. Bass. Paris, 37 (4), pp. 35-44; Morat, P., Le Mouël, J.-L., Nover, G., Will, G., Variation annuelle de la saturation d'une roche de grande porosité induite par la variation saisonnière de la température extérieure et mesurée par voie électrique (1992) C. R. Acad. Sci. Paris, 315, pp. 1083-1090. , Ser. IIa; Morat, P., Le Mouël, J.-L., Poirier, J.-P., Kossobokov, V., Heat and water transport by oscillatory convection in an underground cavity (1999) C. R. Acad. Sci. Paris, 328, pp. 1-8. , Ser. IIa; Morton, B.R., Taylor, G.I., Turner, J.S., Turbulent gravitational convection from maintained and instantaneous sources (1956) Proc. Roy. Soc. London A, 234, pp. 1-23; Perrier, F.,